articles.title: Man Utd continue to back Solskjaer .
articles.body: Ole Gunnar Solskjaer retains the support of Manchester United and is still seen as a long-term appointment, Sky Sports News has been told.Solskjaer has come under fresh scrutiny in the wake of Wednesday's 2-1 defeat at Istanbul Basaksehir in the Champions League - their first in the competition this season.United are currently 15th in the Premier League after losing 1-0 against Arsenal on Sunday, but the club has no plans to replace Solskjaer - despite reports linking former Tottenham manager Mauricio Pochettino with the role at Old Trafford.
articles.author: Brian Oricho
